node.text: The largest of all the spaces we’re updating in the house, the informal living room was under utilized due to an awkward spatial plan that failed to give the room much purpose. Our goal for this space is to provide an inviting, lobby like feel with several sitting areas where resident members will gather between classes, before meals, and at the end of the day. Head to the blog for an even closer look at the changes we’re making to bring our vision to life!

node.title: Tri Delta Traditional // Our Plan for the Informal Living Room

node.text: Install day is just a few weeks a way! Today, we’re taking you through the changes we’re making in the Sunroom at our #trideltatraditional project to breath new life into the original, heavy & dark design. By pulling back and simplifying this space with a timeless color palette & classic finishes, we’re certain that this area will quickly become a favorite for all the member residents at the house.

node.text: We’ve received so many questions regarding the layout of our #sntrideltatraditional project, so today we are taking you through the entire space, room by room. Stay tuned for BIG improvements in the coming weeks and head to the blog to see our BEFORE images + all the inspiration we’re using for the project. Have a question about the changes we’re making? Ask away! 💕

node.text:
Follow along as Jesse takes us through the changes we're making to the Formal Living Room in our #SNTriDeltaTraditional project! Designing this space was all about pulling back and making use of classic materials & timeless style. Floor to ceiling custom millwork alongside white oak hardwood flooring give this living area the light & bright base it deserves. 
See more changes we're making to the formal living room on the blog! https://bit.ly/3fAEu04

node.title: Tri Delta Traditional Remodel | Formal Living Room Update

node.text: The #HinksonHouse Video Tour: Walk through our latest home reveal with S&N founder & designer, Jesse.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Scout & Nimble in Columbia, Missouri with @bodinewhite. May be an image of 1 person, standing and indoor.

node.text: Where do I even begin? Thank you so much for all your support & well wishes on the launch of @bodinewhite. Every comment, text, & message truly meant the world to me & our team. We are so looking forward to sharing more day to day operations at our studio with you & feel incredibly lucky & honored to be helping so many beautiful families with their homes. I never could have dreamed when I was working the night shift as a NICU nurse 14 years ago, that I would be standing here today…launching a second business, living out my passion surrounded by an incredible team and working with the most amazing clients. Thank you for allowing us to continue to do what we love most! 💗

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Scout & Nimble in Columbia, Missouri with @scoutandnimble, and @bodinewhite. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
We think the @bodinewhite launch calls for a celebration -- how about another #snstonebluff sneak peek!? ⁠🥳⁠
⁠
Thank you so much to everyone who has supported us thus far. 💗 We cannot thank you enough for all the love and support we received alongside the @bodinewhite launch today. ⁠
⁠
If you haven't checked out the new @bodinewhite page, head over there and maybe give us a follow while you're there! 😉

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Scout & Nimble on July 19, 2021 tagging @bodinewhite. May be an image of text.

node.text: We have someone we'd like you to meet! Say hello to @bodinewhite 👋🏼 We're thrilled to officially launch our sister design company and can't wait to share all that we've been up to over the past few months!! Head over to their account to show them some love 💗

node.text:
Looking back on one of our all-time favorite kitchens! 😍⁠ That zellige backsplash never fails to put a smile on our faces. ⁠

P.S... You didn't hear it from us but we've got some BIG NEWS coming tomorrow! 👀 Stay tuned!
